@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} S E R V E R   S E T T I N G S @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

This chapter handles all settings that are necessary for a FTP-Site.

· @{B}Comment@{UB} - You can place a comment for a server here.  This could be any
  name that tells you something about the server.

· @{B}Address@{UB} - The domain or IP where the server lives on.
  Must not start with ftp:// as ATC will connect you to a FTP-server
  anyway.

· @{B}Port@{UB} - A portnumber on which ATC should connect the remote server
  If you leave this gadget empty, ATC will use port 21 (hopefully).

· @{B}Mode@{UB} - You can select one of 3 modes here.

  @{B}ADT@{UB} - This is the Aminet-Download-Tool mode. If you connect
  to aminet you want to use this.

  @{B}Login/PW@{UB} - In this mode you give a loginname and a password

  @{B}Anonymous@{UB} - This mode is for anonymous logins like @ftp.vapor.com

· @{B}Remote directory@{UB} - You can put a directory name here, which will be
  visited immediately after a successful login.

· @{B}Checkmark right to "Remote dir."@{UB} - If you check this checkmark, ATC
  will save the name of the last visited directory for this site.

· @{B}PopUp right to "Remote dir."@{UB} - This list contains the last 20 visited
  directories of the remote site.  Doubleclicking an entry will set the
  clicked directory as the remote directory.

· @{B}Local directory@{UB} - Same as remote directory but for local paths.

· @{B}Checkmark right to "local dir."@{UB} - Same as for remote directory (see above)

· @{B}parse URL@{UB} - If you define a new server and write an URL like
  ftp://[username:passwort]@servername[:port]/path into the comment-gadget you
  can use this button to automatically set all fields for the server.

@EndNode
@Node Advanced_Options "AmiTradeCenter: Advanced Options"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} A D V A N C E D   O P T I O N S @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

Advanced options are not vital for a successful login to a remote server.
However, you would probably want to set some of these options to your needs.

· @{B}Tries@{UB} - If a login was not successful (too many users, server not
  reachable or whatever reason) ATC will reconnect as often as you define
  here.

· @{B}Delay@{UB} - Time to wait between every try.

· @{B}Keep Alive@{UB} - ATC send a NOOP-command every 30 seconds.  This will prevent
  you from being disconnected from a remote server because of inactivity.
  Note that this does not work on all servers, i.e.  depends on the remote
  server configuration.

· @{B}Cache@{UB} - If you check this checkmark, ATC will use a cachesystem for this
  server.

· @{B}PASV@{UB} - If you check this checkmark, ATC uses the command PASV instead of
  PORT.  You should use PASV if you are behind a firewall.

· @{B}Single Lister Mode@{UB} - Shows the remote directory only

@EndNode
@Node Transfer_ "AmiTradeCenter: Transfer "
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} T R A N S F E R   @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

· @{B}CPS-Limit@{UB} - This slider limits the CPS.  You can use it if you connect to
  a friend and don't want to use all his bandwidth.  You could also lower the
  CPS to control your own bandwidth.

· @{B}Disconnect if cps drops below@{UB} - If the CPS drops under this limit, ATC
  reconnects you to this server and resume the download.  The aim is to have
  a better CPS after reconnect.

· @{B}for the last (x seconds)@{UB} - Reconnection takes effect if the CPS is
  below the limit for longer then this value, only.

· @{B}Ignore first seconds@{UB} - You can set how many seconds should be ignored for
  the reconnect feature after a new download.  Especially useful if you start
  a download and the CPS is not immediately up to full CPS.  It takes some
  seconds to reach the full CPS with the server.

· @{B}Tries@{UB} - How many times ATC should try to reconnect to achieve a better
  cps.

@EndNode
@Node ADT "AmiTradeCenter: ADT"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} A D T @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

Here you are able to change some functions regarding the ADT-Mode.  If the
serverentry is not in ADT-Mode, this page will be ghosted.

Also see @{"Server" link Server}.


@EndNode
@Node Statistics "AmiTradeCenter: Statistics"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} S T A T I S T I C S @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

This register shows some statistics for the server, such as:

Time and date of your first and last login, the number of connections,
the number of successful logins, the number of files down/uploaded,
the number of bytes sent/received, the maximum and average CPS and
the amount of time you spent on this server.

There's also a button "Clear Statistic" which, of course, set all
statistics to 0 (zero).  This button is only usable if you are not
connected to the server in question.

@EndNode
@Node Server_List "AmiTradeCenter: Server List"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} S E R V E R   L I S T @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

The NList-listview shows all servers that were currently loaded.  You can
read here the comment, the address, the port and the mode of each server.

With a doubleclick of an entry ATC tries to connect to this server.  If you
are already connected to this server, the window jumps to the front or, if
it's iconified it's deiconified.

If you have installed the MUI-Class "NListtree.mcc" you can see the state of
a server from its color.  NListtree.mcc is part of the release-version of
ATC and can be installed during ATC installation quite easily.

Note:  There is also a "real" NListtree.mcc available since a few month.
Please do not install this one because there are too many bugs atm.

Below the server list, there are funny buttons that you can use to
play funny games with each entry.

· @{B}Add Server@{UB} - Adds a server to the end of the list, default settings will
  take effect as configured in settings/server.

· @{B}Copy server@{UB} - ATC adds a copy of the active server to the list.  ATC
  detects automatically how many copies already exist.  E.g.  a server
  called "Aminet USA" would be "C1_Aminet USA" if you hit this button.

· @{B}Remove server@{UB} - Removes a server from the list.

· @{B}Add goup@{UB} - Adds a new group to the end of the list.

· @{B}Connect@{UB} - Tries to connect you to the server (wow).

· @{B}Disconnect@{UB} - Disconnect from the server.

· @{B}(De)Iconify@{UB} - (de)Iconifies the clientwindow (depends on the current
  state of the window.

· @{B}Quit@{UB} - Disconnect the server and shut down the client.


@EndNode
@Node FTP_Window "AmiTradeCenter: FTP Window"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} F T P   W I N D O W @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

This window opens if you try to connect to a server.

The GUI layout depends on your settings.

At the bottom of the window is another list, this is the loglist, where you
can see all activities between ATC and the remote server.  With the right
mousebutton you reach the contextmenu of the loglist and you can select
between "save log as file" or clear loglist.

@EndNode
@Node FTP_ADT-Mode_Menu "AmiTradeCenter: FTP/ADT-Mode Menu"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} F T P / A D T - M O D E   M E N U @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

@{B}@{U} Menu: Project @{UU}@{UB}
· @{B}Server Manager@{UB} - This menu gets the server manager to front.

· @{B}About ATC@{UB} - Dunno

· @{B}About MUI@{UB} - Ditto

· @{B}Disconnect@{UB} - Guess!

· @{B}Quit@{UB} - Guess again ;)

@{B}@{U} Menu: Options @{UU}@{UB}
· @{B}Use cache@{UB} - Please see @{"advanced options" link advanced_options}

· @{B}Keep Alive@{UB} - Please see @{"advanced options" link advanced_options}

· @{B}PASV@{UB} - Please see @{"advanced options" link advanced_options}

· @{B}keep local directory@{UB} - Saves the last used local directory name for the
  next login

· @{B}keep remote directory@{UB} - Dito but for the remote directory

· @{B}show log@{UB} - The loglist at the bottom of the window can be activated here.
  You can either set it to @{B}never@{UB}, @{B}not while downloading@{UB} or simply
  @{B}always@{UB}.  Choose well Luke.

@{B}@{U} Menu: Action @{UU}@{UB}
· @{B}Send raw command@{UB} - You can send any command you want with this menu item.
  If you don't know what to do with this function, better keep your hands
  off!

· @{B}Download by name@{UB} - Here you can download a file by name e.g.
  on aminet in directory /priv/

· @{B}Show Aminet Message Of The Day@{UB} - This is only possible in ADT-Mode.  It
  shows (you wouldn't know if you don't read here) the MOTD in a new window.

@{B}@{U} Menu: Settings @{UU}@{UB}
· @{B}Displaymode Transfer@{UB} - You can select between @{B}simple@{UB} and @{B}detailed@{UB}
  displaymode for downloading.  If you select @{B}simple@{UB}, there will be only a
  few information shown while downloading, whereas @{B}detailed@{UB} shows more
  information.  Just try both modes and decide then ;M)

· @{B}Show remote directory only@{UB} - Change the gui layout to only show the
  remote directory.

@EndNode
@Node FTP-Mode "AmiTradeCenter: FTP-Mode"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} F T P - M O D E @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

The FTP-Mode allows to handle files the way (famous) filemanager does.
You can copy, delete, rename or view a file, you can also create new
directories.

There are 2 listview available for this matter which show your local
directory (left) and the remote directory (right).

Doubleclick an entry either shows the file with the viewer you choose
in ATC-settings or, if the entry is a diretory, change the directory.

On top of every listview you'll find the title of the listview (local or
remote).

· @{B}Strindgadget Path@{UB} - Shows the path that is currently shown in the
  listview.  It is possible to write down a new path here and if it's
  available, ATC changes the directory immediately.

· @{B}PopUp (local)@{UB} - Shows a list with all drives and assigns in your system.
  With a doubleclick you select the drive/assign.

· @{B}PopUp (remote)@{UB} - Shows the last 20 entries of the history from the server.
  With a doubleclick on an entry ATC changes to this old directory.

· @{B}Parent@{UB} - With this button you climb up the tree to the parent directory.

· @{B}Reload@{UB} - If you find out, let me know :-)

@{B}@{U} The Buttons @{UU}@{UB}
· @{B}Send@{UB} (on the left side only) - Uploads all selected entries to the
  selected remote directory.  It is possible to upload a whole directory,
  with its subdirectories as well, to the remote server.  If you indeed have
  selected a directory a requester pops up to ask what you want to do
  exactly.

  @{B}Upload@{UB} - Creates the directory and uploads all files into this new
  (remote) directory.

  @{B}recursive@{UB} - create directory with all its subdirectories on the remote
  server and upload all files.

  @{B}skip@{UB} - Skip this diretory and go to the next entry.

· @{B}Receive@{UB} (remote only) - All seleced files are transferred to the local
  directory.

· @{B}Select@{UB} - With this function you can select files/directories via
  a DOS-pattern (like #?, [1-9] and so on). The window which opens up
  should be pretty self-describing.

· @{B}Makedir@{UB} - Of course, you can create a new directory with this button
  (hey, what did you expect?)

· @{B}Show@{UB} - This starts the viewer you have choosen in ATC-settings for all
  selected entries.

· @{B}Rename@{UB} - If clicked, a requester pops up, where you can enter a new
  name for the active file/directory.

· @{B}Delete@{UB} - Deletes all selected entries.

· @{B}CHMOD@{UB} - CHMOD a remote file. If you don't know what it's good for, just
  don't use it!

@{B}@{U} Statusdisplay @{UU}@{UB}
Below each listview is a textfield where you can see some informations for
the current directory.

This line may look like this:

- @{B}59 Files [2], 16 Dirs [3], 14.505K [4.882K]@{UB} -

That means, there are 59 files with 14.505 kB and 16 directories within the
current directory.  From these entries, 2 files and 3 directories are
selected.  The two files are together 4.882 kB in size.

For the remote listview the statusdisplay also shows CPS and bytes while
reading a remote directory.  You can stop reading directories with the
(wohooo) stopbutton on the right, you will know it's the stopbutton once
you see it.

@EndNode
@Node ADT-Mode "AmiTradeCenter: ADT-Mode"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} A D T - M O D E @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

ADT is a shortcut for Aminet-Download-Tool and is a special mode which
allows to browse a list of recently uploaded files.  Normally this would be
an Aminet-Server.  ATC offers different options in ADT-Mode.

· @{B}Rate Files@{UB} - With this function you can rate a file on Aminet.  The
  charts are maintained on a weekly basis, so don't expect your rating takes
  immediate effect on the charts.  As an Amiga user you should have learned to
  wait, though ;)

· @{B}Show readme@{UB} - If you select a file and hit this button ATC downloads
  and shows the .readme file of the entry.  A doubleclick on an entry has the
  same effect.

· @{B}Select@{UB} - with this function you can select files via a DOS-pattern (like
  #?, [1-9] and so on).  The window which opens should be pretty
  self-describing.

· @{B}Mode@{UB} - There are 6 different modes available.

  · @{B}New@{UB} - This is what you normally want.  It shows all new entries since
    your last login.

  · @{B}Recent 7@{UB}  - Shows all uploads within the last week.

  · @{B}Recent 14@{UB} - Shows all uploads within the last forthnight (2 weeks)

  · @{B}Local@{UB} - Shows all files that are stored on the ADT-Server.  Download
    this list can take some time, be prepared to play tetris or something...
    :)

  @{B}Search@{UB} - You can search through aminet with this function.  Just type
  one or more words into the stringgadget.

  @{B}Charts@{UB} - This mode is not really a standard on ADT-Servers.  There is
  no guarantee that it works on every ADT-Server, at least Wuarchive and
  Paderborn are proofed to work properly.  If you find an ADT-server which
  doesn't work in chart-mode, please report to the ATC-Development-Council(tm).
  However, the charts show 2 lists, one with the most downloaded files and
  one with the highest rated files (ATC tops this list ATM (25.04.2000).

· @{B}Receive@{UB} - Transfer all selected files to your local harddisk.

@{B}@{U} The List @{UU}@{UB}
· @{B}sort@{UB} - To sort the list, just click on one of the titlebars on top
  of the list.

  Of course, in mode "charts" you can't sort the list in any way.

@EndNode
@Node The_Batchlist "AmiTradeCenter: The Batchlist"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} T H E   B A T C H L I S T @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

There are two buttons right under the remote listview.  These two buttons
together builds a powerful feature.  Remembering of files.

· @{B}Add@{UB} - All selected files are gathered in a list if you press this
  button.  There is a mechanism to avoid dupes in the list.  Another
  possibility is to drag&drop the entries over the button or you can
  drag&drop directly into the list if the window is open.

· @{B}PopUp (usually a magnifying glass)@{UB} - With this button you open the
  batchlist which holds the files you have added to the list.

If the list is not empty when you disconnect from a server, ATC can do
different things depending on your settings (see @{"Settings" link Settings}).

@EndNode
@Node Recursive_Download "AmiTradeCenter: Recursive Download"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} R E C U R S I V E   D O W N L O A D @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

A very nice feature of ATC is recursive download.  You can choose if you
want to overtake the directory structure from the remote server (you can
easily mirror a server this way).

If you have indeed selected a directory a new window pops up to ask what
to do.

You have the following choices:

· @{B}Download (flat)@{UB} - Just download all files within the remote directory
  to your download directory.

· @{B}Download (create dir)@{UB} - This method is like download with the difference
  that a new directory is created within your download path.
  All remote files are stored there.

· @{B}Recursive (flat)@{UB} - This method downloads all files, include files that are
  in subdiretories, to your download path.

· @{B}Recursive (keep dirtree)@{UB} - Here it is, the exact mirror function :-)
  The directory structure from the remote server is mirrored on your
  harddisk.

@EndNode
@Node Transfer_Window "AmiTradeCenter: Transfer Window"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} T R A N S F E R   W I N D O W @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

The transfer window is used for up and download.
You can see all necessary data for the up/download here.

The window is somewhat divided in two groups.  The first one shows all data
for the transfer.  The second one show the list of files queued for
transfer and some buttons (while downloading only) as well.

If you start a download ATC will first check if you have enough bytes left
on your harddisk for this particular download.  If this is not the case,
ATC bothers you with a requester to ask what to do.

@{B}@{U} Transfer Group @{UU}@{UB}
You can see vital data here, e.g.  local and remote filename, expected time
for the transfer, expected end of the transfer, elapsed time, cps,
sent/received bytes and some things more (have a look).

· @{B}CPS-Limit@{UB} - During transfer you can control the transfer speed with this
  slider if you e.g. don't want to use too much bandwidth from a friend
  or share your bandwidth with other tasks (like webbrowsers and such).

· @{B}CPS-History@{UB} - You can watch the cps of the last few seconds here.  With
  a doubleclick on the CPS-History you can reset the meter.

· @{B}Abort Transfer@{UB} - Abort the transfer of a file.

  If you have set ATC to ask before aborting a download, a requester pops
  up in the first place. You are asked if you want to go on with downloading,
  abort the download and delete the incomplete file (while downloading only)
  or want to add the file to the batchlist.

@{B}@{U} Batch Group @{UU}@{UB}
This group shows a list with all queued files (waiting for transfer).  On
the right of the list you can see some data about the transfer.

· @{B}Abort Queue@{UB} - Abort the transfer of the queue including the file which
  is in progress at the moment. Again a requester pops up, if your settings
  indicate to do so, asking you what to do.

This would be one of this:

· @{B}Remove Entries@{UB} - Kick selected entries out of the list (big fun indeed ;))

· @{B}Clear List@{UB} - Kick all entries out of the list (even more fun).

· @{B}Add To Batch@{UB} - All entries are added to the batch.

· @{B}Arrow up/down@{UB} - With this buttons you can shuffle the active entry
  up and down within the list.

@EndNode
@Node Settings "AmiTradeCenter: Settings"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} S E T T I N G S @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

This window holds all possible settings for ATC, you find it in the menu
under Settings/Settings (huh).

The setting window is a nice register group to avoid layout mayhem ;)

At the bottom of the window you'll find three buttons which, I think, do
not need to be explained further.


@EndNode
@Node General "AmiTradeCenter: General"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} G E N E R A L @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

· @{B}Closegadget@{UB} - You can set the closegadget of ATC to do different things.

  · @{B}Quit ATC and all connections@{UB} - Does exactly this

  · @{B}Iconify servermanager@{UB} - The servermanager is iconified if you click the
    closegadget

  · @{B}Iconify ATC and Traders@{UB} - The servermanager and all traders are iconified
    if you click the closegadget


· @{B}Password for anonymous logins@{UB} - You can define a password for anonymous
  login here. Usually this is the email address of the user (in this case yours).

· @{B}Viewer@{UB} - You can select your favorite viewer here. This viewer is used
  in FTP and ADT mode to view files (wohooo). You should add %f which will
  be replaced with the filename.

· @{B}Confirm "Remove Server"@{UB} - If you want to remove a server and this
  checkmark is checked, a requester pops up to ask if you really want to do
  this.

· @{B}Backup Profiles@{UB} - ATC backups you profiles at exit if you check this
  checkmark

@EndNode
@Node Transfer "AmiTradeCenter: Transfer"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} T R A N S F E R @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

@{B}@{U} General @{UU}@{UB}
· @{B}Displaymode@{UB} - You can select between simple or detailed layout of the
  transfer window here. (see also @{"FTP/ADT-Mode Menu" link FTP_ADT-Mode_Menu})

@{B}@{U} Download and Download-Queue @{UU}@{UB}

· @{B}Add filenote after download@{UB} - If you check this checkmark, each file
  gets a filenote in form of the URL where it comes from.

· @{B}Confirm "Abort Transfer"@{UB} - You can choose what happens if you abort a
  transfer

  · @{B}Abort Transfer@{UB} - Abort transfer, incomplete files remain on your disk.

  · @{B}Abort And Remove@{UB} - Abort transfer and delete incomplete files from your
  disk.

  · @{B}Add To Batch@{UB} - Abort transfer and add the file to the queue for later
  download. The incomplete file remains on your disk.

· @{B}Confirm Abort Batch@{UB} - You can choose what happens if you
  abort a batch

  · @{B}Abort Queue@{UB} - Abort and delete the current queue.

  · @{B}Add queue and the current download to batch@{UB} - Abort the transfer
    and add all entries from the download queue to the batchlist.

  · @{B}Add queue to batch@{UB} - Abort the transfer and add queue to batchlist

  · @{B}Do Not Abort@{UB} - Guess ;)

· Confirm delete batch - You can choose what happens if you
  delete a batch

  · @{B}Clear Batch@{UB} - Does exactly this ;M)

  · @{B}Move to queue@{UB} - Move all entires to the queue

  · @{B}Do not delete@{UB} - You may figure it out on your own

· @{B}Edit batch before download@{UB} - Before a download is actually started you
  can edit the batch e.g. to receive your most wanted file within the
  batch first or remove one or more files from the queue.

· @{B}Warn if download doesn't fit@{UB} - If you have not enough bytes left on your
  harddisk (where the download should be stored) a requester pops up to
  warn you about that fact.

· @{B}If queue is not empty@{UB} - If the queue is not empty and you try to quit
  the ATC-Trader, you can choose here what to do in this case.

  · @{B}Save Batch@{UB} - Save the queue for the next login and quit ATC-Trader

  · @{B}Download Batch@{UB} - Download the batch right now.

  · @{B}Ignore@{UB} - Ignore the batchlist and quit ATC-Trader.

  · @{B}Ask@{UB} - Ask what to do with the queue

· @{B}Buffersize for download@{UB} - You can set a buffersize for downloading here.
  ATC doesn't write to disk immediately, instead a buffer is filled and if
  the buffer is full ATC writes it to your disk. The buffersize has impact
  on your average CPS, usually bigger buffer means higher CPS.

@EndNode
@Node Switches "AmiTradeCenter: Switches"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} S W I T C H E S @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

· @{B}Confirm Disconnection@{UB} - If this checkmark is checked a requester pops up
  every time you disconnect from a server to ask if you really want to
  disconnect.

· @{B}Confirm local delete@{UB} - If this checkmark is checked a requester pops
  up if you try to delete a local file, i.e. in FTP doublelistmode in
  the left listview that is.

· @{B}Confirm remote delete@{UB} - Same as local but for remote files (of course)

· @{B}Don't activate client window@{UB} - If this checkmark is checked no client
  window will be activated instead, the servermanager remains the active 
  window.

· @{B}Open batch if not empty (after login)@{UB} - If the queue isn't empty after
  a successful login, ATC opens the window with the queue.

· @{B}Show FTP-log@{UB} - You can choose if the loglist is shown @{B}never@{UB},
  @{B}not while transferring@{UB} files or @{B}always@{UB}.

· @{B}Show passwords@{UB} - If this checkmark is checked passwords are shown in
  plain text, otherwise passwords are replaced with three questionmarks (???).

· @{B}Retry to connect also if the server was not reachable@{UB} - This option
  indicates that ATC should retry to connect the server even if it was not
  possible to reach the server (e.g. (61) connection refused).
  Of course ATC tries the connection as often as you defined in
  the settings.

@EndNode
@Node ADT-Settings "AmiTradeCenter: ADT-Settings"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} A D T - S E T T I N G S @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

There are three groups for ADT-Mode.

@{B}@{U} Misc @{UU}@{UB}
· @{B}ADT-Findserver@{UB} - You should define your favorite ADT-Findserver here if
  you want to search through Aminet. Nowadays ftp.wustl.edu would be a
  good thing (tm).

· @{B}max results@{UB} - This slider indicates the maximum entries for searching files

· @{B}ADT-Rate Emailaddress@{UB} - You should write down your (real!) emailaddress here
  if you want to rate files from aminet. The aminetserver will sent you a reply
  to confirm your vote, if your email is invalid, your vote probably would
  not count, you know. Urban is not in charge to sell your emailaddress
  to anyone else nor is he doing strange things or the likes, though.
  Therefore it should be safe to use your real emailaddress here.

@{B}@{U} Highlight Pattern @{UU}@{UB}
If you are looking for some specific files in the first place you can set a
color for these files here.  They will then be displayed in the color you
defined.

· @{B}List@{UB} - You can see all defined patterns here.

· @{B}Add@{UB} - Add a new pattern to the list

· @{B}Remove@{UB} - Remove the active pattern from the list

· @{B}Stringgadget@{UB} - You can edit the pattern here

· @{B}Highlight Color@{UB} - Select a color which should be used for entries that
  match the pattern

@{B}@{U} ADT-Filter @{UU}@{UB}
With aid of ADT-Filter it is possible to skip one or more aminetgroups from
beeing displayed.  E.g.  you never, really never want to see new
WB-Screenshots, just mark /pix/wb to be disabled et viola.  This
can be done with a doubleclick on that group or you use the buttons under
the list.

· @{B}Enable@{UB} - All selected groups will be activated to display new uploads.

· @{B}Disable@{UB} - Now guess ;)

@EndNode
@Node Server "AmiTradeCenter: Server"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} S E R V E R @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

You can predefine new serverentries here, every time you add a new server
this setting will be used by default.

@{B}@{U} Misc @{UU}@{UB}
For more information on this setting see also @{"Server Settings" link Server_Settings} and
@{"Advanced Options" link Advanced_Options}.

@{B}@{U} ADT @{UU}@{UB}
· @{B}Keep Aminet dirtree on local drive@{UB} - If you check this checkmark
  ATC will create exactly the same directories that aminet used to use.
  You can see this as kinda aminetmirrorfunction, useful for e.g. a BBS.

· @{B}Download .readme automatically@{UB} - If this checkmark is checked ATC downloads
  the .readme automatically.

· @{B}Surpress ADT-Logintext@{UB} - If this checkmark is checked ATC does not show the
  Logintext (which could be pretty long on some servers) in the loglist.

· @{B}Show Message Of The Day (MOTD)@{UB} - If this checkmark is checked ATC
  download the MOTD and display it in a seperate window. Note that the
  MOTD is downloaded if it's newer than the last downloaded MOTD only,
  thus you won't see the MOTD all the time.

@EndNode
@Node Events "AmiTradeCenter: Events"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} E V E N T S @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

In this register you can set lotza events for certain conditions.

The conditions are not worth to be explained further, though.  However,
here's what you can configure for every event.

@{B}@{U} List @{UU}@{UB}
This list show all events that can be combined with a sound.

· @{B}Event@{UB} - This column shows the event for which you can add a sound.

· @{B}Deiconify@{UB} - This checkmark indicates that the client should be
  deiconified if the event occours.  Of course a client can be deiconified if
  it's iconified, only.

· @{B}Signal@{UB} - If you want ATC to play a sound for an event you should check
  this checkmark.

· @{B}Sound@{UB} - If signal is checked to be active, you can select a soundfile
  here.  If no file is selected ATC executes a displaybeep and your amiga
  will do whatever you have told her to do in the Workbench preferences.

· @{B}Volume@{UB} - Set the volume for a sound here.

· @{B}The ">" (Jenson) Button ;)@{UB} - This is the testbutton for the event.


@{B}@{U} External player @{UU}@{UB}
· @{B}Use external player@{UB} - ATC plays the sound via datatypes, if you want to
  use another player then check it here.

· @{B}Options for external player@{UB} - You should select your external player
  here. %n is placeholder for the filename and %v for the volume.
  An example is "play16 %n %v".

@EndNode
@Node Colors "AmiTradeCenter: Colors"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} C O L O R S @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

There are three groups where you can select different colors for the
serverlist, the listviews in FTP-Mode and for the CPS-History.

· @{B}Inactive@{UB} - All servers that are not connected will be displayed in this
  color in the Servermanager

· @{B}Disrupted@{UB} - The server will have this color if a connection was
  disrupted for whatever reason.

· @{B}Connect@{UB} - If you start to connect the server, it will get this color.

· @{B}Connected@{UB} - If you are connected to the server it will get this color.

· @{B}Logged in@{UB} - The server gets this color if the login was successful.

· @{B}Download@{UB} - While downloading the server gets this color.

· @{B}Upload@{UB} - While uploading the server gets this color.

· @{B}List@{UB} - If ATC is listing a remote directory the server gets this color.

@{B}@{U} Dirlist colors @{UU}@{UB}
· @{B}Directories@{UB} - Directories are displayed in this color.

· @{B}Files@{UB} - Files are displayed in this color.

· @{B}Links@{UB} - Links are displayed in this color.


@{B}@{U} CPS-History @{UU}@{UB}
The CPS-History is shown in the transfer window and can have the following
colors.

· @{B}Graph@{UB} - The color for the graph of the CPS-History.

· @{B}Background@{UB} - The background of the CPS-History will be in this color.

· @{B}New transfer breakline@{UB} - This color will be used for a breakline if a
  new transfer is started.

· @{B}Show new transfer breakline@{UB} - whether or not you want the new transfer
  breakline to be active or not, set it here.


@EndNode
@Node TETRiS "AmiTradeCenter: TETRiS"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} T E T R I S @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

Select TETRiS in the server manager to play some tetris while downloading.

With the "N" key you start a new game, with the "P" key you pause the game.
With cursor up you flip a tetris-stone about 90 degree to the right, cursor
down moves a stone somewhat faster to the bottomline.  The spacebar drops a
stone completely to the bottomline.

If you click outside the tetris window and thus it is no more the active
window, tetris automatically goes into pause-state.

@EndNode
@Node Support "AmiTradeCenter: Support"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} S U P P O R T @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

@{B}@{U} World Wide Web @{UU}@{UB}
ATC support over WWW can be found at http://amitradecenter.net
You'll also find the latest release as well as betaversions of ATC there.
If you don't, don't hesitate to blame ToDi for the lameness :-)

@{B}@{U} Bugtracker @{UU}@{UB}
Have you discovered a bug in ANR, or want a new feature? Try the AmigaZeux
bugtracker: @{"http://bugs.amigazeux.net/" system "OpenURL URL http://bugs.amigazeux.net/"}.

@{B}@{U} IRC @{UU}@{UB}
You can also directly visit us by pointing your IRC client at
irc.shadowfire.org or irc.amigazeux.de and joining #AmigaZeux.

@EndNode
@Node Known_Bugs "AmiTradeCenter: Known Bugs"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} K N O W N   B U G S @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

There are no known bugs atm.  At least no bugs that, from my point of view,
can be called bugs or they have such nice effects that removing them would
spoil ATC in some way ;)

...uh, ok, there were bugs. Niggling bugs but not fatal ones. They're gone
now. Trust us. (*evil grin*)

@EndNode
@Node Troubleshooting_and_FAQ "AmiTradeCenter: Troubleshooting and FAQ"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} T R O U B L E S H O O T I N G   A N D   F A Q @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

Okay, you got me.  There is one problem I'm not very fond of.  If you are
using the patched Listtree.mcc (patched to use NList) on small screens
(640*480 and smaller) you can be assured that ATC will crash.  The solution
to this problem is, to somehow make the class (resides in mui:libs/mui)
undiscoverable for ATC.  You can do this by either rename it, delete it or
move it to another directory. The name of the class is NListtree.mcc.

ATC doesn't like the OS-patch NitrOS (or maybe NitrOS doesn't like ATC).
If you want to use NitrOS in conjunction with ATC, be assured that this
won't be an easy task and will cause problems. [Thanks to BKJ]

@{B}@{U} Frequently Asked Questions @{UU}@{UB}
Q: The log is too big.  Could you please reduce the size to 60% of
   actually height. (or something like this)

A: There is a balance-object between the log and the upper GUI, so
   you can set the size of the log by yourself. I suggest you to download
   betterbalance.mcc from Aminet, which, in contrary to the original
   balance class remembers the balance settings of the GUI.

-------

Q: If I change the colors of the busy-bar, why won't they be taken over?

A: I assume you changed the colors from the ServerManager.
   If yes, you have to change the colors from the MUI-prefs of every trader.
   That's because ATC (ServerManager) and the Trader are two separate
   applications in terms of MUI and save their prefs to different files.

-------

Q: Everytime I change the font in the MUI-Prefs, ATC uses a different
   font.  Why doesn't ATC use the font I selected?

A: ATC has a BIG GUI so MUI cannot layout it with your selected font.
   Simply change the screen resolution to a bigger size and all should work
   okay.

@EndNode
@Node Hints "AmiTradeCenter: Hints"
@{B}______________________________________________________________________________@{UB}
@{B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{BG SHADOW} H I N T S @{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT}@{UB}@{BG Shadow}   @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow}  @{BG Background} @{BG Shadow} @{BG Background} |@{UB} |  |
@{B}@{FG Highlight}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{UB}@{FG Text}

· Patch Listtree.mcc to NListtree.mcc
  You must not really do this on your own because the installer should have
  copied the NListtree.mcc already, except you deny the question during
  installation (there's no good reason to do that).

  @{B}Background@{UB}:  ATC actually makes use of listtree.mcc in the
  servermanager.  This MUI-Class is unable to display single entries in free
  configurable colors.  At the beginning of development, as ATC managed the
  list via NList.mcc, the colorstuff was already implemented into the
  servermanager to show the state for every server, that was no problem with
  NList.mcc.

  Solution: To get back the nice colorstuff into the serverlist, you load
  the file Listtree.mcc into a texteditor. You then look for 'list.mui',
  remove the 0-byte after 'list.mui' and replace 'list.mui' with 'NList.mui'.
  Save the file as 'mui:libs/mui/NListtree.mcc and you're done.

· Convert AmFTP serverlist:  To use the serverlist you have used in AmFTP
  there is a short Arexx-script to do the job.

  @{B}Instructions@{UB}: You start AmFTP (for the last time in the next couple of decades)
  open a Shell and change the directory to the path where the script is
  stored, by default this is <your path:>AmiTradeCenter/Utilities.  How to
  change the current directory can not be explained any further because this
  a long planned skill-test for everyone ;) If you indeed managed to change
  the current directory (wooohooo, cool), write down in the shell 'rx
  AmFTP2ATC.rexx' and press return very heavy (in case it works a little bad
  these days).

  The script then gets all entries out of the AmFTP serverlist and saves them
  in a format that is acceptable for ATC as 'ram:ATC.Profiles'.  If you
  managed all these magic steps, you can close AmFTP and start ATC.

  You then select the menu 'server/profiles/Add Profiles. A requester pops
  up where you can, with an amazing ease, select the profiles file which is
  still stored in ram:ATC.profiles.

· @{B}ADT-Find@{UB}: If you're in charge for a special archive it is recommended
  to use more than one word to look for. E.g. you are looking for the MUI-Class
  Busy.mcc. You should use 'busy mui' as keywords for the search process.
  You'll see that very little archives will be found that way
  (that's what you want if you are looking for a special archive, isn't it ;)).

@EndNode
